This paper deals with optimizing network utility in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The addition of trust values to the optimization framework is a security measure, which could also place the paper under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also deals with delay constraints, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of optimization techniques to achieve decomposition by duality or the primal-dual method is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the integration of community-based monitoring and trust values could involve the use of machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
